1 dism issal bell at the end of the school day to end instructional
2 time; and
3 2. “Personal electronic device” means a personal device capable
4 of connecting to a smart phone, the Internet, or a cellular or Wi-Fi
5 network, or directly connecting to another similar device. Personal
6 electronic devices include, but are not limited to, smart watches,
7 smart headphones, laptops, tablets, and smart glasses. Personal
8 electronic devices shall not include school-issued or school-
9 approved devices that are specifically limited for use in classroom
10 instruction.
11 B. 1. For the 2025-2026 school year, each school district
12 board of education shall adopt a policy prohibiting students from
13 using cell phones and personal electronic devices while on the
14 campus of a public school district from bell to bell. The policy
15 shall include disciplinary procedures for violations.
16 2. For the 2026-2027 school year and each school year
17 thereafter, each school district board of education may adopt a
18 policy prohibiting students from using cell phones and personal
19 electronic devices while on the campus of a public school district
20 from bell to bell.
21 C. The policy adopted pursuant to subsection B of this section
22 may provide for exceptions including, but not limited to:
23 1. Emergency use of cell phones or personal electronic devices
24 by students during the school day; and
